article.headline: Utah State 81, UC Davis 55
article.story: LOGAN, Utah (AP) -- Spencer Nelson scored 18 points Saturday to lead Utah State to an 81-55 win over UC Davis. Nelson was perfect from the field, 6-for-6, and pulled down a team-high 10 rebounds. Utah State (3-1) also set a team record for field goal percentage, shooting 28-for-36 (77.8 percent), eclipsing a 18-year-old record, though they missed nine free throws in the game. A scrambling perimeter defense by UC Davis (1-1) forced Utah State into 18 turnovers but also led to numerous layups and inside baskets for the home Aggies, particularly in the second half when Utah State had 11 layups. Cass Matheus added 16 points for Utah State. UC Davis was led by Fowzi Abdelsamad with 20 points, 12 of which came from 3-point shots. Ryan Moore added 13. In the first half, the teams traded leads early until a steal and breakaway layup by Marques Crane gave Utah State a 9-7 lead. The Aggies led by as many as 17 points in the first half, and took a 39-24 lead into the locker room. Utah State shot 5-of-7 from beyond the 3-point line and outrebounded the smaller UC Davis Aggies 24-19. Playing as an independent, UC Davis plays 17 games against Big West opponents this season and will become a member of that conference in the 2007-08 season.
